# Trivy ignore file for the agent + agent-hub image scans
# (.github/workflows/agent-image-scan.yml, agent-hub-image-scan.yml).
#
# Only REVIEWED, non-actionable findings belong here, each with a reason. Any
# HIGH/CRITICAL not listed here still fails the scan — this is a triage list,
# not a mute button. Revisit entries when the upstream fix reaches our base image.

# --- Bundled npm internals in the upstream node:22 base image ---
# picomatch and sigstore ship inside the base image's GLOBAL npm (npm's own
# node_modules), not our code. Neither service runs npm at runtime: agent-hub is
# stdlib-only `node server.js`, and the agent uses npm only at build time to
# install claude-code. So these are not reachable exposure, and no node:22 tag
# yet bundles the patched npm. Drop these once node:22 ships the fixes.

# picomatch 4.0.3 ReDoS — fixed upstream in 4.0.4
CVE-2026-33671
# sigstore 3.1.0 (cert OID verification) — fixed upstream in 4.1.1
CVE-2026-48815
